<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Publications Associate</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Publications Associate<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Julie Hertzog<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, Non-exempt
</p>

<h3>Responsibilities:</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Produce quality, accurate and appealing layout and print design for communication, marketing and information.</li>
	<li>Concept and develop the layout of printed projects including; brochures, newsletters, books, flyers, handouts, promotional materials, signs, etc.</li>
	<li>Determine print specifications.</li>
	<li>Work with print representatives to obtain competitive print bids, preflight press jobs, and follow through on print production.</li>
	<li>Design layout and format of presentations using Power Point.</li>
	<li>Perform organizational tasks of various projects; verifying information, contacting organizations for benefit ads, etc.</li>
	<li>Edit/proof material for correct grammar, spelling, punctuation, and format consistency.</li>
	<li>Maintain timelines on production workflow.</li>
	<li>Other duties as may be required.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Requirements:</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Post secondary degree required</li>
	<li>Ability to think creatively and use independent judgment</li>
	<li>Above average technical proficiency in;  Adobe In Design | Adobe Illustrator | Adobe Photoshop | Adobe Acrobat </li>
	<li>Working knowledge of Microsoft Office (PowerPoint and Word)</li>
	<li>Knowledge of prepress and experience working with print representatives</li>
	<li>Strong organizational skills</li>
	<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
	<li>Accuracy and attention to detail</li>
	<li>Ability to prioritize and complete projects within timelines </li>
	<li>Ability to work independently and participate in team planning and decision-making process</li>
	<li>Knowledge of/sensitivity to issues related to persons with disabilities</li>
	<li>Ability to get along well with others</li>
</ul>

<p>
Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
Salary will be based on experience and qualifications. Position is open until filled.
</p>

<p>Submit resume with cover letter to:<br />
Sandy Loehnis | PACER Center | 8161 Normandale Blvd | Minneapolis, MN 55437
</p>

